00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:43,480
And the other person wants to say something to you, say, hang on.
而另一个人想对你说点什么，就说，等一下。

167
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,480
Hang on.
等一下。

168
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,480
Wait a moment.
等一会儿。

169
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:46,480
I have to tell you this thing.
我得告诉你这件事。

170
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:49,540
So you wouldn't really use it with your boss or a customer.
所以你通常不会对老板或客户用这个。

171
00:07:49,540 --> 00:07:50,960
You wouldn't say, hang on a second.
你不会说，等一下。

172
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:54,960
No, you would say that with a friend or family member, things like that.
不，你会对朋友或家人说这类话。

173
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:58,840
OK, so it's a very informal way of saying, wait a moment.
好的，所以这是一种非常非正式的说法，意思是“等一会儿”。

174
00:07:58,840 --> 00:07:59,840
Wait a minute.
等一分钟。

175
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:00,840
That's right.
没错。

176
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:02,260
So the formal way is, please wait.
所以正式的说法是，请稍等。

177
00:08:02,260 --> 00:08:03,260
Please wait.
请稍等。

178
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:05,240
And the informal way is, hang on.
而非正式的说法是，等一下。

179
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:06,240
Hang on.
等一下。

180
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:08,880
Or hang on a sec, which is hang on a second.
或者“hang on a sec”，也就是“hang on a second”。

181
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:09,880
All right.
好的。

182
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:11,920
That's all the words we have for today.
这就是我们今天要讲的所有内容。

183
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:15,000
Why don't we review our dialogue one last time?
我们最后再复习一遍对话好吗？

184
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:21,840
Ugh, this bathroom is a pig's die.
呃，这卫生间脏得像猪圈。

185
00:08:21,840 --> 00:08:24,280
Helen, why do you keep flushing the toilet?
海伦，你为什么老冲马桶？

186
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:25,280
What's wrong?
怎么了？

187
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:26,720
I just can't stand it.
我就是受不了。

188
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:28,200
It's really gross in here.
这里太恶心了。

189
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:32,320
There's a stain on the toilet seat and the floor was wet and slippery, so I cleaned it.
马桶座上有污渍，地板又湿又滑，所以我清理了一下。

190
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:33,920
You did what?
你做了什么？

191
00:08:33,920 --> 00:08:38,840
Helen, I know it's gross, but I've seen many public washrooms that are much worse.
海伦，我知道很恶心，但我见过比这糟糕得多的公共卫生间。

192
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,320
Why are you cleaning the countertop?
你为什么在擦台面？

193
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:42,840
Are you out of your mind?
你疯了吗？

194
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:43,840
I can't help myself.
我控制不住自己。

195
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,680
It's just so disgusting in here.
这里实在太恶心了。

196
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:48,640
Helen, this is not like your own bathroom.
海伦，这又不是你自己的卫生间。

197
00:08:48,640 --> 00:08:50,400
Just leave it to the cleaners, OK?
留给清洁工处理吧，好吗？

198
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,400
Hang on.
等一下。

199
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:53,200
I'm just going to quickly wipe the sink and sweep the floor.
我很快擦一下水槽，再扫个地。

200
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:55,000
You're such a neat freak.
你真是个洁癖狂。

201
00:08:55,000 --> 00:09:03,840
I'm out of here.
我走了。

202
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:10,000
All right, so talking about cleanliness and being neat, what type of person are you?
好的，说到清洁和整洁，你是什么类型的人？

203
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,320
Are you a neat freak?
你是洁癖狂吗？

204
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:13,920
Do you keep everything very clean and ordered?
你会把一切都保持得非常干净和有序吗？

205
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:19,040
I'm not a neat freak, but I'm also not a pig, not a slob.
我不是洁癖狂，但也不是猪，不是邋遢鬼。

206
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:21,760
I like things to be very organized.
我喜欢东西井井有条。

207
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:25,400
But I'm not really concerned about cleaning so much.
但我其实不太在意打扫。

208
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:26,400
I'm too lazy.
我太懒了。

209
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:28,280
So there's a difference for me.
所以对我来说有区别。

210
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:33,200
In my house, I know where everything is, but maybe there's clothes on the floor and there's
在我家，我知道每样东西在哪里，但可能地上有衣服，

211
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:35,640
books in the bathroom.
浴室里有书。

212
00:09:35,640 --> 00:09:36,640
So I'm in the middle.
所以我处于中间状态。

213
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:37,640
What about you?
你呢？

214
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:38,640
Are you a neat freak?
你是洁癖狂吗？

215
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:44,240
No, I'm not really a neat freak per se, but I do like everything to be very clean, on
不，我严格来说不是洁癖狂，但我确实喜欢一切都很干净，

216
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:45,240
the other hand.
另一方面。

217
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:48,440
So I can't really stand it when things are...
所以我真的受不了东西...

218
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:52,600
If things are out of order a little bit, that's okay, but if things are dirty, that really
如果东西有点乱，那还行，但如果脏了，那真的

219
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,600
gets to me.
让我受不了。

220
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:59,960
But I'm not the type of person that has folders with all my bills in one folder or labels,
但我不是那种把所有账单都放在一个文件夹里或贴标签的人，

221
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:02,880
or even when I was in school, I didn't have my notebooks in order.
甚至上学时，我的笔记本也不是整整齐齐的。

222
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:03,880
Really?
真的吗？

223
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:04,880
So we're the opposite.
那我们正好相反。

224
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:06,280
Yeah, exactly.
是的，没错。

225
00:10:06,280 --> 00:10:08,720
But I hate things that are dirty.
但我讨厌脏东西。

226
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:09,720
Interesting.
有意思。

227
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:12,160
Well, let us know, are you a neat freak?
好吧，告诉我们，你是洁癖狂吗？

228
